GAUTENG cops have arrested five people including a foreigner, his wife and girlfriend. The suspects were arrested for their alleged involvement in the kidnapping of a Midrand businessman on 18 January. Police spokeswoman Brigadier Athlenda Mathe said following the kidnapping, the suspects demanded ransom from the victim’s family and business associates. They were arrested at residential properties between Tshwane and Joburg.  “A Toyota Corolla and Quantum, used in the commission of the crime, have been seized together with multiple phones and SIM cards,” Mathe said. You must be SIGNED IN to read comments  “Additionally, at this year’s National Excellence Awards over the weekend in Limpopo, the national anti-kidnapping task team was awarded the 2021/2022 Crime Intelligence Team of the Year award for its role in preventing, combating, investigating and apprehending those behind kidnappings. To date, more than 124 suspects have been arrested, with 81 still in police custody,” she added.